{
  "text": "Oxygen was the first parameter chosen to be measured in our study due to its importance in general cell health and metabolism. While difficult to measure, the instrumentation required to detect oxygen consumption on a single-cell scale set the stage for detection of other molecules of interest to biologists. The MLSC has developed a system that is capable of measuring the oxygen consumption rate of a single cell with fmol/minute resolution [CITATION_1] . The measurement is performed by sealing individual cells in a microchamber and optically probing a Pt-porphyrin sensor located inside the micromachined micro-wells.",
  "citation_candidates": [
